X:1
T:Grace plus breath MuseScore-compat regression
C:abc2xml relocates breath marks off grace notes
% REGRESSION TEST for the MuseScore 4 grace-plus-breath import crash.
% MuseScore 4 segfaults when a breath mark is attached to a grace note.
% abc2xml applies a decoration to the next note event, so a phrase-end breath
% written just before a pickup grace would otherwise attach to that grace note.
% fixGraceBreaths() relocates it onto the preceding real note instead.
% PASS: after conversion, no note has BOTH a grace child AND a breath mark, and
% all breath marks survive (relocated, not dropped). The music line below has 3
% breath marks; exactly one falls before a grace and must be relocated.
% Check (must print 0):
%   awk '/<note>/{g=b=0} /grace/{g=1} /breathANDmark/{b=1} /\/note/{if(g+b==2)c++} END{print c+0}' out.xml
M:4/4
L:1/8
Q:1/4=70
K:C
V:Fl clef=treble name="Flute"
{C}(!tenuto!D3 D A2 A2|!tenuto!A3 A {d}e2 e2) !breath!|({f}!tenuto!e3 d !mordent!B2 A2|!tenuto!d6) !breath!z2|{A}(!tenuto!A3 A e2 e2|!tenuto!e3 d {e}c2 A2)|(!tenuto!G3 A !turn!F2 E2|!tenuto!D6) !breath!z2|]
